  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2018-01-30",
    "date": "2019-08-02T15:31:15Z",
    "text": "This bill amends the Safe Drinking Water Act to require the Environmental Protection Agency to establish a grant program that assists local educational agencies in replacing drinking water fountains located in schools or day care facilities with fountains that are lead-free. Grant recipients may also use funding for monitoring and reporting lead levels in the drinking water of schools or day care facilities."
